text: The 2019 Norfolk State Spartans football team represented Norfolk State University in the 2019 NCAA Division I FCS football season. They were led by fourth-year head coach Latrell Scott and played their home games at William "Dick" Price Stadium. They were a member of the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference (MEAC). They finished the season 5–7, 4–4 in MEAC play to finish in fifth place. ==Previous season== The Spartans finished the 2018 season 4–7, 2–5 in MEAC play to finish in a tie for eighth place. ==Preseason== ===MEAC poll=== In the MEAC preseason poll released on July 26, 2019, the Spartans were predicted to finish in seventh place. {| class="wikitable" |- align="center" |- align="center" | 1 || North Carolina A&T; || 304 (12) |- align="center" | 2 || Bethune–Cookman || 237 (1) |- align="center" | 3 || Florida A&M; || 204 (2) |- align="center" | 4 || Howard || 166 |- align="center" | 5 || North Carolina Central || 161 (1) |- align="center" | 6 || South Carolina State || 152 |- align="center" | 7 || Norfolk State || 119 (1) |- align="center" | 8 || Morgan State || 87 (1) |- align="center" | 9 || Delaware State || 46 |} ===Preseason All–MEAC teams=== The Spartans had six players selected to the preseason all-MEAC teams.
